data.enText: to make a position of power or success stronger so that it is more likely to continue

data.chText: 他新执导的影片巩固了他作为全国最佳导演的地位。
data.enText: With this new movie he has consolidated his position as the country's leading director.

data.chText: 意大利队的第二个进球巩固了其领先的地位。
data.enText: Italy consolidated their lead with a second goal.
to join things together into one; to be joined into one
All the debts have been consolidated.

data.chText: 为提高效率，这两家公司已合并。
data.enText: The two companies consolidated for greater efficiency.
the consolidation of Japan's banking industry

example: consolidate one's hold on first place

tr: make or form into a solid or hardened mass
form into a solid mass or whole
bring together into a single whole or system
example: The town and county schools are being consolidated

value.def: If you consolidate something that you have, for example power or success, you strengthen it so that it becomes more effective or secure.

example.ex: The question is: will the junta consolidate its power by force?...
example.tran: 问题是：军政府会通过武力巩固其政权吗？

example.ex: Brydon's team-mate Martin Williamson consolidated his lead in the National League when he won the latest round.
example.tran: 布赖登的队友马丁·威廉森在最近一轮比赛中获胜，巩固了自己在全国联赛中的领先地位。

example.ex: But change brought about the growth and consolidation of the working class...
example.tran: 但是变革使得工人阶级发展壮大起来。

example.ex: Even if not total, the Romans' hold was sufficient for them to begin the task of consolidation.
example.tran: 即使没有实现完全的控制，罗马人的势力也足以让他们开始着手巩固政权了。

value.def: To consolidate a number of small groups or firms means to make them into one large organization.

example.ex: Judge Charles Schwartz is giving the state 60 days to disband and consolidate Louisiana's four higher education boards...
example.tran: 查尔斯·施瓦茨法官将给路易斯安那州60天时间来解散然后合并该州的4个高等教育委员会。

example.ex: IBM, which consolidated some operations last summer, has made clear that it needs to continue to streamline them.
example.tran: 去年夏天合并了部分业务的IBM公司明确表示需要继续进行精简，以提高效率。

example.ex: This consolidation meant having to reduce the numerical strength of the Army...
example.tran: 这次合并意味着不得不削减陆军的兵力。

example.ex: Further consolidations in the industry could follow.
example.tran: 该产业随后可能会有进一步的合并。
